在[[電腦科學|電腦科學]]和[[數學|數學]]裡面，一個'''隨機樹'''是一個經由[[隨機過程|隨機過程]]建立的[[樹_(資料結構)|樹]]或者[[樹狀圖_(資料結構)|樹狀圖]](arborescence)。

隨機樹有以下幾種類別：

*{{link-en|循環擦除隨機走仿#均勻生成樹|Loop-erased_random_walk#Uniform_spanning_tree|均勻生成樹}}（Uniform spanning tree）<!--, a spanning tree of a given graph in which each different tree is equally likely to be selected-->
*[[隨機最小生成樹|隨機最小生成樹]]（random minimal spanning tree）<!--, spanning trees of a graph formed by choosing random edge weights and using the minimum spanning tree for those weights-->
*{{link-en|隨機二元樹|Random binary tree}}<!--, binary trees with a given number of nodes, formed by inserting the nodes in a random order or by selecting all possible trees uniformly at random-->

*{{link-en|遞迴樹#隨機遞迴樹|Recursive tree#Random recursive tree|隨機遞迴樹}}（Random recursive tree）<!--, increasingly labelled trees, which can be generated using a simple stochastic growth rule. -->

*[[Treap|Treap]]或者說隨機二元搜尋樹<!--，a data structure that uses random choices to simulate a random binary tree for non-random update sequences-->
*{{link-en|選擇性快速拓展隨機樹|Rapidly-exploring random tree}}（Rapidly-exploring random tree）<!--, a fractal space-filling pattern used as a data structure for searching high-dimensional spaces-->
*{{link-en|布朗樹|Brownian_tree}}（brownian tree）<!--, a fractal tree structure created by diffusion-limited aggregation processes-->
*[[隨機森林|隨機森林]]<!--，一種 machine-learning classifier based on choosing random subsets of variables for each tree and using the most frequent tree output as the overall classification-->
*{{link-en|分枝過程|Branching_process}}<!--, a model of a population in which each individual has a random number of children-->

